The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 August is 67,065 (7,729.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 August, there were 2,604 new confirmed cases (300.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 August, there were 2,548 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 2% (56 extra cases).
